String Functions 
A String is a character oriented datatype that holds the 
text of unlimited length. A Variable is a location in memory 
for storing data. There are different types of data types in 
ABAP:
1) I - Integer
2) C - Character 
3) String - String Datatype 
4) Packed Decimals - for storing decimal points
Data is the keyword for defining a variable in 
ABAP.
String Functions.
1) Concatenate joins one or more strings.
2) Translate translates the string to upper and lower cases.
3) Replace is the function that replaces one character with 
another character.
4) Condense is the function that removes the leading spaces 
in the string.
5) Strlen is the function used to find the length
of the string.
