Internal tables 
An internal table is a dataset located in the 
working memory space of ABAP.It is like an 
Array in other programming languages.An 
internal table allocates the space at run time.
Every internal table has 3 parts:
1) Header line/ Work area/ Line Type/ 
Structure that stores a single line or 
row.
2) Key which is unique or non-unique.
3) Table Type / Body that stores multiple 
records or a table.
 There are 3 types of Table Types
1) Standard Table 
2) Sorted Table 
3) Hashed table
The below example is for storing the 
information of the structure for vendor details 
which contains the following fields.
Vendorno,Vendorname,City and Country and with 
the data mentioned below.
 
1003 Demo Vendor3 Hyderabad IN
Workarea/ Structure/Line 
type/Headerline
Body / Table Type
1) Standard Table
2) Sorted Table
3) Hashed Table
 There are various operations of an internal 
table which are as mentioned below:
1) Append 
2) Sort
3) Read table
4) Clear
5) Refresh
6) Free
7) Collect 
Each record from the workarea must be appended 
to the body of the internal table.
There are 2 ways of creating an internal table:
1) An internal table with header line where 
the workarea and body will have same 
names.
It is created using the keyword OCCURS.
OCCURS defines an internal table.
Syntax:Begin of Vendor occurs 0,
 <fld1>,
 <fld2>,
1001 Demo Vendor 1 Hyderabad IN
1002 Demo Vendor 2 Delhi IN
1003 Demo Vendor 3 Chennai IN
 <fld3>,
 End of Vendor.
0 is the number of records allocated.
When 0 is mentioned the space is 
allocated for unlimited number of 
records.
If occurs 10 is given,space is allocated 
for 10 and so on.
