Classical Reports 
Classical Reports are those reports where an 
input is provided and its corresponding output 
is displayed.
Every ABAP Program has 3 parts:
1) Declaration section where all the 
variables are declared.
2) Processing section where the processing 
is done.
3) Output section where the output is 
displayed.
 The following are the events in the classical 
 Reports:
1) Initialization is an event where all the 
variables are declared or initialized.
It is used for providing the default 
values in the program.
2) AT Selection screen is used for 
validating the user input in the 
selection screen.
3) Start of selection is used for further 
processing when the selection screen 
leaves.It is normally used for database 
processing(retrieving the data from the 
tables)
4) End-of-selection is used for displaying 
the output.
5) Top-of-page is used for providing the 
column headings in the output.
6) End-of-page is used for providing the 
displaying the footer details in the 
output.
