Sub Routines 
Sub Routines are reusable objects where once created can 
be used by other objects.There are 2 types of Sub 
routines.
Sub routines that are called within the program are 
called as Internal Sub routines and the sub routines 
that are called outside are called as External Sub 
routines.
A Sub routine is called in the program with the 
following syntax:
PERFORM <Sub_routinename>.
<Sub_routinename> is the name of the sub routine.
PERFORM is the keyword that defines the sub routine.
The implementation of the sub routine is done with the 
following syntax:
FORM <Sub_routinename>.
For ex:
PERFORM Sub_Validate.
Sub_Validate is the name of the sub routine.
The implementation of the sub routine Sub_Validate has 
the following syntax:
PERFORM Sub_Validate – Calling or defining the sub 
routine
FORM Sub_Validate.
ENDFORM.
