Interactive Reports 
Interactive reports are those reports where navigation takes 
place from screen to another screen. The classical reports 
are static in nature(fixed) in output whereas interactive 
reports are dynamic in nature. Screen to screen navigation 
is possible .The first output screen is called as Basic
List, the second output screen is called as First Primary 
list and so on.A Maximum of 20 screens navigation is 
possible in these reports.
The following are the events in an Interactive Reports:
1) At line selection triggers when any column in the row is 
selected and navigates to next screen.
2) At User-command triggers when a button is clicked and 
further action is to be taken.
3) Set Pf-status is used for creating GUI Status.
4) Top-of-page during line-selection is used for providing 
the Column headings in the interactive lists.
 Hide and Get Cursor are the methods used in Interactive 
reports.
