Function Modules 
Function modules are reusable objects where once created 
can be used by other objects.Function Builder is the 
tool for creating function modules.A Function group 
needs to be created before creating a function module.
99 function modules can be created in a single function
group.There are seven tabs in a function module.
1) Attributes defines the type of function module.
2) Import defines the Input that is passed in the 
 function module.
3) Export defines the return parameter in the function 
 module.
4) Changing defines the result and return parameter and
 that changes in run time.
5) Tables defines the internal table parameter that is 
 defined in the function module.
6) Exceptions defines the error handling mechanism in 
 function module.
7) Source Code defines the code to be written for the 
 interface in the function module.
Note:When the function module is called in the 
program,the import becomes the export parameter and the 
export becomes the import parameter.
