ALV 
ALV Stands for ABAP List Viewer which is a tool for 
controlling the output of the program.It is very 
difficult for the developer to write the code for 
formatting the output like coloring,sorting etc.SAP has 
provided a library called as SLIS(Standard list) that 
contains all the declartions of ALV which are to be 
mapped to the function modules mentioned below.The 
following are some of the important parameters in SLIS 
library.
1) Field catalog --- all the fields must be added to the 
 field catalog 
2) Layout --- layout as to how the output must be 
 displayed.
3) Sorting --- how the field must be sorted.
The parameters mentioned above must be mapped to the 
standard function modules provided below:
1) REUSE_ALV_LIST_DISPLAY---DISPLAYS THE OUTPUT IN A 
 LIST FORMAT 
2) REUSE_ALV_GRID_DISPLAY --- DISPLAYS THE OUTPUT IN A 
 TABLE FORMAT 
3) REUSE_ALV_HIERSEQ_LIST_DISPLAY --- DISPLAYS THE 
 OUTPUT IN A HIERARCHIAL FORMAT 
4) REUSE_ALV_COMMENTARY_WRITE --- DISPLAYS THE DATA IN 
 THE HEADER 
5) REUSE_ALV_POPUP_TO_SELECT --- DISPLAYS THE OUTPUT IN 
 A POPUP.
6) REUSE_ALV_BLOCK_LIST_INIT---INITIALIZES THE BLOCK
7) REUSE_ALV_BLOCK_LIST_APPEND---APPENDS THE DATA IN THE
 BLOCK.
8) REUSE_ALV_BLOCK_LIST_DISPLAY---DISPLAYS THE OUTPUT 
 IN A BLOCKED FORMAT.
